If `parent[i] == i`, return $i$ (root).
Otherwise, recursively call $\text{Find}(\text{parent}[i])$.
Crucially, update `dist[i]` during path compression. If $R = \text{Find}(\text{parent}[i])$, the old path was $i \to \text{parent}[i] \to R$. The new path is $i \to R$.
New $\text{dist}[i]$ = Old $\text{dist}[i] \oplus \text{dist}[\text{parent}[i]]_{\text{old}}$.
Update $\text{parent}[i] = R$. Return $R$.

